it wo n't earn the franchise many new fans , but saw VI is a surprising step up for what has become an intricately grisly annual tradition .
even if you are n't a fan , beyond the mat provides a riveting , perceptive look into the world of professional wrestling by taking a closer look at the people beneath the personas .
the movie that catapulted ang lee into the ranks of upper echelon hollywood filmmakers , crouching tiger , hidden dragon features a deft mix of amazing martial arts battles , beautiful scenery , and tasteful drama .
delightful and strangely moving .
a funny and clever reshaping of emma , clueless offers a soft satire that pokes as much fun at teen films as it does at the beverly hills glitterati .
with a deliciously wicked performance from angelica huston and imaginative puppetry by jim henson 's creature shop , nicolas roeg 's dark and witty movie captures the spirit of roald dahl 's writing like few other adaptations .
tackling a sensitive subject with maturity , honesty , and wit , obvious child serves as a deeply promising debut for writer-director gillian robespierre .
all about steve is an oddly creepy , sour film , featuring a heroine so desperate and peculiar that audiences may be more likely to pity than root for her .
overdosing on flashbacks , and more portentous than profound , the overly obtuse premonition weakly echoes such twisty classics as memento , the sixth sense , and groundhog day .
slow , cheap-looking , and dull , season of the witch fails even as unintentional comedy .
gwyneth paltrow and anthony hopkins give exceptional performances in a film that intelligently tackles the territory between madness and genius .
rocky iv inflates the action to absurd heights , but it ultimately rings hollow thanks to a story that hits the same basic beats as the first three entries in the franchise .
flawed but fascinating , cast away offers an intelligent script , some of robert zemeckis ' most mature directing , and a showcase performance from tom hanks .
bread and tulips is a sweet-natured comedy offering gentle , escapist entertainment .
tense , complex , and drenched in atmosphere , phoenix is a well-acted , smartly crafted war drama that finds writer-director christian petzold working at peak power .
breathless rewrote the rules of cinema -- and more than 50 years after its arrival , jean-luc godard 's paradigm-shifting classic remains every bit as vital .
full of endearing characters , this doc about a choir of `` seniors behaving badly '' is uplifting and delightful .
gentle and nostalgic , from up on poppy hill is one of studio ghibli 's sweeter efforts -- and if it does n't push the boundaries of the genre , it remains as engagingly lovely as ghibli fans have come to expect .
director christian alvert has a certain stylish flair , but it 's wasted on case 39 's frightless , unoriginal plot .
bridge to terabithia is a faithful adaptation of a beloved children 's novel and a powerful portrayal of love , loss , and imagination through children 's eyes .
epic in technical scale but breathlessly intimate in narrative scope , boyhood is a sprawling investigation of the human condition .
a dark but timely subject is handled deftly by writer/directer owen moverman and superbly acted by woody harrleson and ben foster .
bela lugosi 's timeless portrayal of dracula in this creepy and atmospheric 1931 film has set the standard for major vampiric roles since .
marc singer 's documentary about a group of homeless people living beneath the streets of new york city is haunting and uplifting in equal measure .
sweet smell of success boasts a top-notch cast , sharp direction , atmospheric cinematography , and an appropriately jazzy score , making it one of the best noir crime thrillers ever made .
the graphic details of jesus ' torture make the movie tough to sit through and obscure whatever message it is trying to convey .
a sensual thriller with two engaging performers demanding our undivided attention .
anne hathaway and julie andrews bring charm and elegance to the movie , but there 's not enough material for them to work with in this sequel .
at some point in the conversation , god must have asked for a subtler , deeper film .
led by a charming performance from paul rudd , ant-man offers marvel thrills on an appropriately smaller scale -- albeit not as smoothly as its most successful predecessors .
smart , tightly wound , and solidly acted , margin call turns the convoluted financial meltdown of '08 into gripping , thought-provoking drama .
even though the story is overly familiar , there 's enough here for an engaging ride .
with a fascinating real-life story and powerhouse performances from angela bassett and laurence fishburne , what 's love got to do with it ? is a ca n't miss biopic .
the cliched characters and obvious outcome make all the fun and excitement amount to nothing .
undeniably lowbrow but surprisingly sly , revenge of the nerds has enough big laughs to qualify as a minor classic in the slobs-vs . - snobs subgenre .
it stumbles into melodrama , but i am love backs up its flamboyance with tremendous visual style and a marvelous central performance from tilda swinton .
it misses perhaps as often as it hits , but jim carrey 's manic bombast , cameron diaz ' blowsy appeal , and the film 's overall cartoony bombast keep the mask afloat .
while not the comprehensive profile of the man that his die-hard fans might have hoped for , gonzo remains an insightful introduction to the life of rebellious writer hunter s. thompson and his influences .
a provocative historical fiction about the early days of psychoanalysis , a dangerous method is buoyed by terrific performances by michael fassbender , keira knightley , and viggo mortensen .
a threadbare story anchored by strong performances , then she found me is a mostly successful directorial debut by helen hunt .
sweet , empathetic , and shot through with a palpable joy , we are the best ! offers a tender tribute to the bittersweet tumult of adolescence .
the aura is a highly original and cerebral thriller that maintains its suspense from start to finish .
not only does this documentary introduce viewers to glennie , it gives them a taste of how she perceives the world .
smart , fascinating , and funny , best of enemies takes a penetrating -- and wildly entertaining -- look back at the dawn of pundit politics .
wwjb is an eye opening doc about consumerism that manages to be both funny and informative .
anchored by smart , sensitive direction and strong performances , complicance is a ripped-from-the-headlines thriller that 's equal parts gripping and disturbing .
under the assured direction of alfonso cuaron , harry potter and the prisoner of azkaban triumphantly strikes a delicate balance between technical wizardry and complex storytelling .
earns its 6 hours running time by telling an engrossing story with compelling characters .
this highly derivative superhero coming-of-age flick is moderately entertaining , family-friendly fluff .
playing jack frost as an evil cross between liza minnelli and liberace , martin short is a welcome presence , but this tired series continues drawing from its bag of bland gags and dumb slapstick .
a small , sensitive , and moving portrait of a teacher and his students .
the second james bond film , from russia with love is a razor-sharp , briskly-paced cold war thriller that features several electrifying action scenes .
don jon proves to be an amiable directing debut for joseph gordon-levitt , and a vivacious showcase for his co-star , scarlett johansson .
using music and home video footage to great effect , jonathan caouette has made a very personal and moving film .
jason statham and ben foster turn in enjoyable performances , but this superficial remake betrays them with mind-numbing violence and action thriller cliches .
made-for-tv drama evokes anything but real emotion .
flawed but eminently watchable , joel schumacher 's teen vampire thriller blends horror , humor , and plenty of visual style with standout performances from a cast full of young 1980s stars .
john travolta and nicolas cage play cat-and-mouse -lrb- and literally play each other -rrb- against a beautifully stylized backdrop of typically elegant , over-the-top john woo violence .
though sometimes melodramatic and formulaic , north country is nonetheless a rousing , powerful story of courage and humanity .
a compelling story cleverly told , we are what we are quenches horror buffs ' thirst for gore while serving up serious-minded filmmaking and solid acting .
penetrating rivers ' coarse image , this compelling documentary offers an honest , behind-the-scenes look at her career -- and at show business in general .
smart , original , and horrifically funny , teeth puts a fresh feminist spin on horror movie tropes .
though it does n't quite answer all of the questions it raises , winnebago man is nevertheless a fascinating , hilarious , and surprisingly poignant look at a geniunely colorful internet celebrity .
although becoming jane is a well-crafted period piece , it lacks fresh insight into the life and works of jane austen . the film focuses too much on wardrobe and not enough on austen 's achievements .
with the requisite combination of humor , sorrow and outstanding visuals , the darjeeling limited will satisfy wes anderson fans .
graceful and bittersweet , queen and country finds writer-director john boorman revisiting past glories with warmth and wisdom .
crude and offensive , but with ample cultural insights and gut-busting laughs , bruno is another outlandish and entertaining mockumentary from sacha baron cohen .
mary shelley 's frankenstein is ambitious and visually striking , but the overwrought tone and lack of scares make for a tonally inconsistent experience .
oceans adds another visually stunning chapter to the disney nature library .
befitting its unorthodox origins , this bad lieutenant benefits from werner herzog 's typically fearless direction and a delightfully unhinged nicolas cage in the title role .
mr. nobody 's narrative tangles may bedevil as much as they entertain , but its big ambitions and absorbing visuals make for an intriguing addition to director jaco van dormael 's filmography .
a dryly comic , stylistically brave film .
ambitious to a fault , the place beyond the pines finds writer/director derek cianfrance reaching for -- and often grasping -- thorny themes of family , fatherhood , and fate .
the twilight saga 's second installment may satisfy hardcore fans of the series , but outsiders are likely to be turned off by its slow pace , relentlessly downcast tone , and excessive length .
perhaps the most faithful of disney 's literary adaptations , this cute , charming collection of episodes captures the spirit of a.a. milne 's classic stories .
nicole holofcener 's newest might seem slight in places , but its rendering of complex characters in a conflicted economic landscape is varied , natural , and touching all the same .
tim burton 's alien invasion spoof faithfully recreates the wooden characters and schlocky story of cheesy '50s sci-fi and ed wood movies -- perhaps a little too faithfully for audiences .
bland characters , clichéd dialogue and rickety plotting ensure we own the night never lives up to its potential .
though its characterizations are weaker than usual , treasure planet offers a fast-paced , beautifully rendered vision of outer space .
its action may be bit too over-the-top for some , but die another day is lavishly crafted and succeeds in evoking classic bond themes from the franchise 's earlier installments .
more slow-moving than run lola run , this film nonetheless offers an intriguing storyline about love and fate .
this compassionate work of social criticism is also luminous , due to both its lyrical imagery and cast .
pocahontas means well , and has moments of startling beauty , but it 's largely a bland , uninspired effort , with uneven plotting and an unfortunate lack of fun .
the others is a spooky thriller that reminds us that a movie does n't need expensive special effects to be creepy .
with its plot about child kidnapping and endangerment , trapped is an exploitative thriller , more queasy than suspenseful .
the life and times of hank greenberg is an affectionate , often very funny portrait of a baseball pioneer .
should satisfy young teens , but offers nothing new for those who are familiar with the formula .
despite an interesting premise -lrb- and a starmaking turn from vin diesel -rrb- , pitch black is too derivative and formulaic to fully recommend to sci-fi or action fans .
solaris is a haunting , meditative film that uses sci-fi to raise complex questions about humanity and existence .
a cheerfully energetic screwball comedy , only human milks laughs from its culture-clash premise .
kaurismהki delivers another droll comedy full of his trademark humor .
it does n't offer any twists on the predictable courtroom thriller formula , but with a charming matthew mcconaughey leading its solid cast , the lincoln lawyer offers briskly enjoyable entertainment .
vacancy 's restraint with gore is commendable , the thin characters and b-movie cliches less so .
it 's far from his most thought-provoking work , but tabloid finds errol morris as smart , spirited , and engaging as ever .
funny , clever , and endearingly unusual , frank transcends its quirky trappings with a heartfelt -- and surprisingly thought-provoking -- story .
it may be shamelessly derivative and overly nostalgic , but the sandlot is nevertheless a genuinely sweet and funny coming-of-age adventure .
violent , quirky , and darkly funny , fargo delivers an original crime story and a wonderful performance by mcdormand .
artfully composed , powerfully acted , and fueled by a powerful blend of anger and empathy , the killing fields is a career-defining triumph for director roland joffé and a masterpiece of american cinema .
though it begins with promise , hancock suffers from a flimsy narrative and poor execution .
despite good performances by cage and especially by leoni , the family man is too predictable and derivative to add anything new to the christmas genre . also , it sinks under its sentimentality .
i 'm going home is a masterfully subtle and poignant exploration of mortality .
a real polarising movie , this gallic torture-porn is graphic , brutal , nasty and gruesome and not to everyone 's taste .
clerks ii dishes up much of the graphic humor and some of the insight that made the 1994 original a cult hit .
the crow : city of angels is a sloppy pretender that captures neither the mood nor energy of the original .
a remarkable achievement , playtime 's packs every scene with sight gags and characters that both celebrates and satirizes the urbanization of modern life .
a fun , whimsical tale about an office drone trying to save his life from his narrator , stranger than fiction features a subdued performances from will ferrell that contributes mightily to its quirky , mind-bending affect .
a traditional genre western , appaloosa sets itself apart with smart psychology , an intriguing love triangle , and good chemistry between the leads .
despite johnny depp 's zealous performance , muddled direction and murky cinematography hinder the libertine .
john schlesinger 's gritty , unrelentingly bleak look at the seedy underbelly of urban american life is undeniably disturbing , but dustin hoffman and jon voight 's performances make it difficult to turn away .
this modest , unpretentious character study astutely captures the emotional states of the 20-something slacker .
though joshua is ultimately too formulaic , its intelligence and suspenseful buildup heighten the overall creep factor .
sophisticated visual effects fail to offset awkward performances and an uneven script .
sylvester stallone knows how to stage action sequences , but the movie 's uneven pacing and excessive violence -lrb- even for the franchise -rrb- is more nauseating than entertaining .
arthur kane is a fascinating subject in what ultimately proves to be a touching , bittersweet documentary .
the vertical ray of the sun is gorgeously , poetically composed , lulling the viewer into its story of everyday life .
this story of politics , race and , sexual awakening has moments that pack a punch , but overall , towelhead never quite achieves the nuance of helmer alan ball 's television work .
a bland , fluffy , and predictable bit of wish fulfillment .
despite the gimmicky feel of the split narratives , the movie is watch-able due to the winning performances by the cast .
sleek , loud , and over the top , fast five proudly embraces its brainless action thrills and injects new life into the franchise .
ang lee 's lust , caution is a tense , sensual and beautifully-shot espionage film .
despite its stylized and impressive sets , this horror-monster movie mish-mash suffers from endless cliches and wildly implausible plotlines .
m night shayamalan 's the sixth sense is a twisty ghost story with all the style of a classical hollywood picture , but all the chills of a modern horror flick .
excellent cinematography and an interesting plot accompanied by a talented cast and crew make u-571 a tense thriller .
with miscast leads and unoriginal , uninspired dialogue , the last legion pales in comparison to the recent cinematic epics it invokes .
kung fu panda has a familiar message , but the pleasing mix of humor , swift martial arts action , and colorful animation makes for winning summer entertainment .
it suffers from comparisons to its predecessor -- not to mention tony jaa 's less-than-nimble direction -- but ong bak 2 has all the extravagant violence and playful style that fans of the original will expect .
still unnerving to this day , frankenstein adroitly explores the fine line between genius and madness , and features boris karloff 's legendary , frightening performance as the monster .
it may evoke memories of classic summer blockbusters a little too eagerly for some , but super 8 has thrills , visual dazzle , and emotional depth to spare .
cheesy , unnecessary remake .
a kick-ass addition to the cop-buddy film genre .
the bodyguard is a cheesy , melodramatic potboiler with occasional moments of electricity from whitney houston .
though the film stays true to the nature of the original cartoon , the script is disappointing and not funny .
though it begins promisingly enough , the fluffer eventually descends into melodrama .
fantastic acting and crisply choreographed action sequences propel this unique , cool take on the revenge thriller .
a moving coming-of-age tale that captures the despair among england 's working-class youth in the 1980s .
thanks to the spirited performances of a talented cast - particularly will ferrell and jon heder as rivals-turned-teammates -- blades of glory successfully spoofs inspirational sports dramas with inspired abandon .
even though it 's based on a true story , coach carter is pretty formulaic stuff , but it 's effective and energetic , thanks to a strong central performance from samuel l. jackson .
at times a tense and provocative thriller , civic duty struggles to move beyond its one-note premise .
though made with care and affection for its characters , the big year plods along , rarely reaching any comedic heights .
critics say that if you 're willing to suffer through soap opera-like dialogue and plot to see some excellent dancing , this movie is for you . otherwise , you might be better off renting fame .
while youthful miley fans wo n't complain , hannah montana the movie is little more than a formulaic disney channel episode stretched thin .
lucas needs to improve on the plot and character development , but there 's plenty of eye candy to behold .
when not overusing sight gags , slapstick , and richard pryor , superman iii resorts to plot points rehashed from the previous superman flicks .
madcap and heartfelt , edgar wright 's apocalypse comedy the world 's end benefits from the typically hilarious simon pegg and nick frost , with a plethora of supporting players .
this absorbing but wince-inducing documentary is a cautionary tale about the costs of hubris in the world of indie film .
it 's often painful to watch , but rabbit hole 's finely written script and convincing performances make it worth the effort .
see spot run has all the elements chidren enjoy in a movie : a lovable dog , bad things happening to stupid adults , and lots of dog poop . for adults , it 's either hit-or-miss .
the movie raises the bar for computer animated movies , but the story is dull and emotionally removed .
straight outta compton is a biopic that 's built to last , thanks to f. gary gray 's confident direction and engaging performances from a solid cast .
a well-acted , eccentric civil war film , ang lee 's ride with the devil is often more visually striking than it is emotionally engaging .
filled with inspired silliness and quotable lines , anchorman is n't the most consistent comedy in the world , but will ferrell 's buffoonish central performance helps keep this portrait of a clueless newsman from going off the rails .
john huston proves an odd choice to direct , miring annie in a sluggish , stagebound mess of an adaptation , but the kids are cute and the songs are memorable .
though it requires patience to view , what time is it there ? 's exploration of loneliness is both elegant and haunting .
a surprisingly conventional romantic comedy from kevin smith , jersey girl is warm but often overly sentimental
bolstered by nolte 's strong performance , the good thief brims with seductive style .
hard-hitting , absorbing , and painfully relevant , the overnighters offers an urgent and compassionate picture of life in 21st century america .
the main stars are absolutely perfect in this absorbing , existential drama that dissects human relationships .
a chilling true crime drama , foxcatcher offers steve carell , mark ruffalo , and channing tatum a chance to shine -- and all three of them rise to the challenge .
though it may not be as comprehensive as some would like , francis ford coppola 's cheerful biopic of the failed automotive designer features sparkling direction and a strong central performance from jeff bridges .
besides bringing on the laughs , barbershop displays a big heart and demonstrates the value of community .
a muddled brain-teaser , stay has a solid cast and innovative visuals but little beneath the surface .
with death-defying action sequences and epic historic sweep , hero offers everything a martial arts fan could ask for .
powerfully directed and acted , '71 stays true to its fact-based origins while remaining as gripping as any solidly crafted action thriller .
though some may find its conclusion unsatisfying , changing lanes is a tense , well-crafted exploration of meaty ethical dilemmas .
magic mike 's sensitive direction , smart screenplay , and strong performances allow audiences to have their beefcake and eat it too .
well-acted if monotonous drama about a transvestite prostitute in london during the 1970s .
steep is a mixed bag of breathtaking mountain footage and yawn-inducing banter .
louder , campier , and more incoherent than its predecessors , blade : trinity seems content to emphasize style over substance and rehash familiar themes .
me you them tells a warmly comical and touching story , and features a charismatically earthy performance by casж .
underutilizing a talented cast , mr. woodcock lacks the comic energy and timing to make the most of its intriguing premise .
restrained but disturbing , a tale of two sisters is a creepily effective , if at times confusing , horror movie .
blandly inoffensive and thoroughly predictable , mr. popper 's penguins could have been worse -- but it should have been better .
a romantic dramedy with boring , stock characters and contrived situations .
led by henrik ruben ganz 's assured direction , this knotty danish noir thriller steers audiences into some nicely unexpected territory .
plagued by paper-thin characterizations and a hackneyed script , material girls fails to live up to even the minimum standards of its genre .
though the film may not delve as deep as some would prefer , more than a game is an inspiring documentary featuring likable youngsters , a positive message , and some exciting in-game footage .
you can count on me may look like it belongs on the small screen , but the movie surprises with its simple yet affecting story . beautifully acted and crafted , the movie will simply draw you in .
at once beholden to the established conventions of the genre and delightfully subversive of them , ip man is one of the most exciting -- and refreshingly character-driven -- martial arts films in years .
breathtaking visuals and dynamic performances make the diving bell and the butterfly a powerful biopic .
jamie lee curtis and lindsay lohan charm in mark waters ' nicely pitched -- and disney 's second -- remake of the 1976 hit .
silly premise notwithstanding , this is a well-made hollywood movie : thrilling and exciting action with just enough characterization .
results moves stubbornly at its own deliberate pace , but the well-chosen cast -- and writer-director andrew bujalski 's insightful observations -- offer rich rewards for patient viewers .
this sequel is full of lavish costumes and elaborate sets , but lacks the heart and creativity of the original elizabeth
next friday lacks the fun of the original friday . the movie is messy and plotless and relies on unfunny vulgar gags .
this story of a down-on-his-luck boxer is thoroughly predictable , but sylvester stallone 's script and stunning performance in the title role brush aside complaints .
the cast is solid and it 's visually well-crafted , but mars needs moms suffers from a lack of imagination and heart .
trembling before g-d looks at the effects of religious morality on believers whose sexuality falls outside the accepted norm with intelligence and compassion .
robots delights on a visual level , but the story feels like it came off an assembly line .
puzzlingly misguided , neil labute 's update the wicker man struggles against unintentional comedy and fails .
exhilarating and intense , this high-impact chase thriller is a model of taut and efficient formula filmmaking , and it features harrison ford at his frantic best .
tommy lee jones 's searing performance helps to elevate cobb above your typical sports biopic ; he 's so effective , in fact , that some may find the film unpleasant .
though it does n't approach the depth of the best animated films , monsters vs. aliens has enough humor and special effects to entertain moviegoers of all ages .
an overblown thriller with formulaic action scenes and poor acting .
unconventional and refreshing , this strikingly un-hollywood film takes a quiet and heartbreaking look at the warmth and inspiration of friendships lost .
john waters ' musical ode to the teen rebel genre is infectious and gleefully camp , providing star johnny depp with the perfect vehicle in which to lampoon his pin-up image .
the rare tearjerking melodrama with sociopolitical subtext , coming home plucks the heartstrings with thought-provoking power .
a thin plot is disguised by high octane dancing and action in this bollywood crossover comedy .
a clever , offbeat romantic comedy , 500 days of summer is refreshingly honest and utterly charming .
george lazenby 's only appearance as 007 is a fine entry in the series , featuring one of the most intriguing bond girls in tracy di vincenzo -lrb- diana rigg -rrb- , breathtaking visuals , and some great ski chases .
although the film is n't as bad as feared -lrb- it was n't pre-screened for reviews -rrb- , it 's not that good , either . most noticable flaws are the sappy romantic cliches and lack of chemistry between gere and ryder .
the scenery is nice to look at , and julia roberts is as luminous as ever , but without the spiritual and emotional weight of the book that inspired it , eat pray love is too shallow to resonate .
a charming piece of work with believable characters .
chilly and haunting , yella 's atmosphere gets under the skin .
despite some fine performances , the kite runner is just shy of rendering the magic of the novel on to the big screen .
director bujalski continues to give cinematic voice to awkward , literate twentysomethings with noteworthy smarts and tenderness .
jet li 's arrival breathes fresh life into a tired franchise formula -- but not enough to put lethal weapon 4 on equal footing with its predecessors .
a coming-of-age drama entwined with a political statement , in bloom underscores its well-worn themes with strong performances and palpable real-world tension .
witty and provocative .
monsieur lahzar is a tender and thoughtful portrait of a man with hidden grief and also a compelling exploration of the teacher-student dynamic .
as formulaic as sports movies get , this underdog story still triumphs on the strength of its inspiring story .
proudly profane and splendidly silly , dodgeball is a worthy spiritual successor to the goofball comedies of the 1980s .
absurd characters and quirky gags are brought to life by a talented cast , providing this superhero spoof with lots of laughs .
the setup is intriguing , but mr. brooks overstuffs itself with twists and subplots , becoming more preposterous as it goes along .
the story of an aging movie actress ' complicated personal saga unfolds in this sophisticated anime film that deftly blurs memory and make-believe into a meditation on the nature of cinema itself .
dizzyingly original , the loopy , multi-layered adaptation is both funny and thought-provoking .
plumbing the depths of tragedy without succuming to melodrama , chang-dong lee 's secret sunshine is a grueling , albeit moving , piece of beautifully acted cinema .
brilliantly filmed and fueled with classic physical comedy , the general captures buster keaton at his timeless best .
socially minded yet entertaining , the day the earth stood still imparts its moral of peace and understanding without didacticism .
a short sketch 's worth of jokes stretched into a full-length feature .
keep the lights on is a mysterious , sexy journey deep into the love affair of two men that always manages to stay true to life .
starting out in the evening features sharp dialogue and moving performances from the talented frank langella and lili taylor .
dancer in dark can be grim , dull , and difficult to watch , but even so , it has a powerful and moving performance from bjork and is something quite new and visionary .
greenberg 's title character is harder to like than most , but ben stiller 's nuanced performance and a darkly funny script help take the misanthropic edge off .
a visually lovely epic with compelling , three-dimensional characters .
arnold schwarzenegger tries his best , but jingle all the way suffers from an uneven tone , shifting wildly from a would-be satire on materialism to an antic , slapstick yuk-fest .
a touching , uplifting and inspirational rockumentary about an aging metal band , both hilarious and heart-warming in equal measure .
kate beckinsale is as lovely as ever , and does her best with the material , but moribund pacing and an uninspired plot leave whiteout in the cold .
its script may not be as dazzling as its eye-popping visuals , but scott pilgrim vs. the world is fast , funny , and inventive .
this teen romance flick feels like a predictable rehashing of other movies .
guardians of the galaxy is just as irreverent as fans of the frequently zany marvel comic would expect -- as well as funny , thrilling , full of heart , and packed with visual splendor .
kenneth branagh 's sprawling , finely textured adaptation of shakespeare 's masterpiece lives up to its source material , using strong performances and a sharp cinematic focus to create a powerfully resonant film that wastes none of its 246 minutes .
the royal tenenbaums is a delightful adult comedy with many quirks and a sense of poignancy . many critics especially praised hackman 's performance .
in terms of the gangster genre , empire 's story is yet another tired retread .
thanks to the cast , ghostbusters 2 is reasonably amusing , but it lacks the charm , wit , and energy of its predecessor .
a thoroughly engrossing documentary examining the life of talented but troubled writer charles bukowski .
even though the film is stylish and atmospheric , critics say the ninth gate meanders aimlessly and is often ludicrous . and despite the advertising , there 's hardly any chills .
jennifer garner inhabits her role with earnest gusto , but elektra 's tone deaf script is too self-serious and bereft of intelligent dialogue to provide engaging thrills .
effectively balancing humor and subtle pathos , sofia coppola crafts a moving , melancholy story that serves as a showcase for both bill murray and scarlett johansson .
a bona fide classic of midnight cinema , tommy wiseau 's misguided masterpiece subverts the rules of filmmaking with a boundless enthusiasm that renders such mundanities as acting , screenwriting , and cinematography utterly irrelevant . you will never see a football the same way again .
riveting and bone-chillingly creepy , cropsey manages to be one of the best documentaries and one of the best horror movies of the year .
beautiful , thoughtful , and engrossing , jiro dreams of sushi should prove satisfying even for filmgoers who do n't care for the cuisine .
it 's sexist , juvenile , and dated , but heavy metal makes up for its flaws with eye-popping animation and a classic , smartly used soundtrack .
the hot chick 's one-note concept gets stretched thin , and a lot of the jokes fall flat .
far from the madding crowd invites tough comparisons to thomas hardy 's classic novel -- and its previous adaptation -- but stands on its own thanks to strong direction and a talented cast .
raw , brutal , and bitter , cartel land offers a ground-level look at vigilante efforts to thwart organized crime at the mexican-american border .
a quiet but moving film anchored by the unexpected depth of ashley judd 's performance .
the animation is as eye-popping as ever , but happy feet two 's narrative is too noisily incoherent to recapture the oscar-winning charm of its predecessor .
though it has an excellent cast , this emotionally detached movie is the kind that one admires more than enjoys .
both a smart , suspenseful tale of intrigue and a sweeping romance , the year of living dangerously features excellent performances from mel gibson and sigourney weaver as a pair of journalists covering political unrest in indonesia .
meet the robinsons is a visually impressive children 's animated film marked by a story of considerable depth .
french director andré téchiné successfully weaves five gripping stories in an engaging and realistic film about the early days of the aids epidemic .
with the help of its charismatic lead , some impressive action sequences , and even a few surprises , iron man 3 is a witty , entertaining adventure and a strong addition to the marvel canon .
manderlay may work better as a political statement than as a film , making its points at the expense of telling a compelling story .
whether you think this mentally ill cult musician is worthy of being called a `` genius , '' this document of his life is crafted with sincere respect and is fascinating to watch .
beautifully written , sensitively directed , and powerfully acted , the past serves as another compelling testament to asghar farhadi 's gift for finely layered drama .
it may not rank with scorsese 's best work , but shutter island 's gleefully unapologetic genre thrills represent the director at his most unrestrained .
perfectly cast and packed with suspense , the hunt for red october is an old-fashioned submarine thriller with plenty of firepower to spare .
kickin ' it old skool is one big unfunny pop culture reference that does n't feature many laughs .
martin lawrence lends his comedic touch , but the movie is n't much more than standard action-comedy fare .
it 's hard not to admire its unabashed sentimentality , but the notebook is too clumsily manipulative to rise above its melodramatic clichés .
it makes good on the old-school action it promises , but given all the talent on display , the expendables should hit harder .
anchored by mads mikkelsen 's sympathetic performance , the hunt asks difficult questions with the courage to pursue answers head on .
a wickedly funny tale of three witches and their duel with the devil , fuelled by some delicious fantasy and arch comedic performances .
big budgets and costumes in service of scatalogical jokes may seem funny on paper , but in execution this is a highly monotonous romp that registers only occasional laughs .
a compelling look at stephen glass ' fall from grace .
superbly acted and satisfyingly engaging , your sister 's sister subverts rom-com conventions with sensitive direction , an unconventional screenplay , and a big heart .
filmed and presented on a scale not seen in modern productions , gone with the wind is , if not the definitive hollywood film , then certainly near the top of the list .
a remarkable technical achievement , metropolis ' eye-popping visuals more than compensate for its relatively routine story .
michael clayton is one of the most sharply scripted films of 2007 , with an engrossing premise and faultless acting . director tony gilroy succeeds not only in capturing the audience 's attention , but holding it until the credits roll .
director ridley scott re-edits his 1979 sci-fi classic to produce an elegantly re-mastered film that is as terrifying and effective as ever .
graceful , complex , and beautifully layered , fill the void offers a sympathetic portrait of an insulated culture by exploring universal themes .
with a workplace-related theme worthy of satire , the promotion features some sharp witticisms but ultimately disappoints .
featuring outstanding performances from john malkovich and newcomer jessica haines , disgrace is a disturbing , powerful drama .
thanks to a script that ephasizes its heroes ' humanity and a wealth of superpowered set pieces , the avengers lives up to its hype and raises the bar for marvel at the movies .
delivering a quirky spin on familiar twentysomething tropes -- with a cannily-placed soundtrack -- garden state has enough charm to mark a winning debut for first-time director zach braff .
an entertaining , topical thriller that finds director tony scott on solid form and will smith confirming his action headliner status .
death race 2000 is a fun , campy classic , drawing genuine thrills from its mindless ultra-violence .
driven by michael moore 's sincere humanism , sicko is a devastating , convincing , and very entertaining documentary about the state of america 's health care .
the white ribbon effectively utilizes tension and a bleak atmosphere to deliver a thought-provoking examination of nascent fascism .
despite fine work by an appealing cast , it 's complicated is predictable romantic comedy fare , going for broad laughs instead of subtlety and nuance .
ashley judd and morgan freeman make this predictable affair watchable .
bolstered by a strong performance from matthew mcconaughey in the title role , mud offers an engaging southern drama that manages to stay sweet and heartwarming without being sappy .
bolstered by powerful lead performances from javier bardem , josh brolin , and tommy lee jones , no country for old men finds the coen brothers spinning cinematic gold out of cormac mccarthy 's grim , darkly funny novel .
dallas buyers club rests squarely on matthew mcconaughey 's scrawny shoulders , and he carries the burden gracefully with what might be a career-best performance .
unfunny and unoriginal . in other words , a perfect piece of evidence for opponents of pointless movie sequels .
exuberant and eye-popping , avengers : age of ultron serves as an overstuffed but mostly satisfying sequel , reuniting its predecessor 's unwieldy cast with a few new additions and a worthy foe .
cary fukunaga directs a fiery and elegant adaptation of charlotte bronte 's classic novel , and mia wasikowska delivers possibly the best portrayal of the title character ever .
a well-acted , intensely shot , action filled war epic , kathryn bigelow 's the hurt locker is thus far the best of the recent dramatizations of the iraq war .
the lyrical baran is a moving film , both for its love story and political underpinnings .
funny and poignant social critique of german reunification .
jacques demy elevates the basic drama of everyday life into a soaring opera full of bittersweet passion and playful charm , featuring a timeless performance from catherine deneuve .
as thought-provoking as it is thrilling , looper delivers an uncommonly smart , bravely original blend of futuristic sci-fi and good old-fashioned action .
the age of adaline ruminates on mortality less compellingly than similarly themed films , but is set apart by memorable performances from blake lively and harrison ford .
semi-pro is an intermittently funny , half-hearted attempt at sports satire , and one of will ferrell 's weaker cinematic efforts .
critics say stuart little is charming with kids and adults for its humor and visual effects .
this teen horror movie brings nothing new to an already exhausted genre . and it 's bad . really bad .
complex , human characters and on-location shooting give beyond the gates palpable tension and urgency .
despite some fine performances and memorable scenes , fast food nation is more effective as eric schlosser 's eye-opening non-fiction book than as richard linklater 's fictionalized , mostly punchless movie .
bleak and uncompromising , but director ken loach brightens his film with gorgeous cinematography and tight pacing , and features a fine performance from cillian murphy .
a film that tackles something as simple as everyday life and succeeds beatifully . the witty script and clever direction keep the film flowing , while the superb acting keeps it alive . it does n't aim for the sky and for that reason it hits its mark .
the cast brings after the wedding 's melodramatic script to life , creating a movie that is emotionally raw and satisfying .
whatever it takes is another run-of-the-mill teeny-bopper romance flick . cliche jokes and a tired plot capture few laughs .
dummy is a sweet family comedy that succeeds due to charming performances , even if the final product feels slightly undercooked .
team america will either offend you or leave you in stitches . it 'll probably do both .
on the strength of its two lead performances assassination is an expertly crafted period piece , and an insightful look at one of the enduring figures of american lore .
wes craven 's intelligent premise , combined with the horrifying visual appearance of freddy krueger , still causes nightmares to this day .
smart , original , and above all terrifying , it follows is the rare modern horror film that works on multiple levels -- and leaves a lingering sting .
its jokes are profoundly bold and rude but incredibly funny at the same time .
warm bodies offers a sweet , well-acted spin on a genre that all too often lives down to its brain-dead protagonists .
powerfully moving and emotionally resonant , wild finds director jean-marc vallée and star reese witherspoon working at the peak of their respective powers .
though laurence sterne 's novel was considered more or less impossible to successfully adapt to film , director michael winterbottom has done it in tristram shandy : a cock and bull story , by making movie about the making of the movie . stars steve coogan and rob brydon add madcap , knowing performances to the mix , and the result is a fun , postmodern romp , before there was any modern romp to post .
less nuanced than its source material , memoirs of a geisha may be a lavish production , but it still carries the simplistic air of a soap opera .
TRON legacy boasts dazzling visuals , but its human characters and story get lost amidst its state-of-the-art production design .
a concise , entertaining documentary about the spectacular failure of enron .
fueled by powerful acting and a taut , patiently constructed narrative , 99 homes is a modern economic parable whose righteous fury is matched by its intelligence and compassion .
jim carrey 's comic convulsions are the only bright spots in this otherwise dim and predictable comedy .
with elements that seem borrowed from movies like goodfellas and boogie nights , blow is pretty much been-there-done-that despite another excellent performance from johnny depp . it , also , becomes too sentimental at the end .
guillermo del toro crafts a stellar comic book sequel , boasting visuals that are as imaginative as the characters are endearing .
lucky you tries to combine a romantic story with the high-stakes world of poker , but comes up with an empty hand .
terrence malick 's singularly deliberate style may prove unrewarding for some , but for patient viewers , tree of life is an emotional as well as visual treat .
taking full advantage of the large imax screen , ultimate x is a thrill ride for extreme sports junkies and novices alike .
happy accidents has enough quirkiness and charm to rise above the more formulaic entries in the romantic comedy genre .
g-force features manic action , but fails to come up with interesting characters or an inspired plot .
revealing yet respectful , 20,000 days on earth is essential viewing for any nick cave fan .
director ang lee revisits the ennui-laden decadence of 1970s suburban america with deft humor and gripping pathos .
if under the same moon is often manipulative , it is also heartfelt , and features strong performances from its leads .
unnecessarily violent and unflinchingly absurd , law abiding citizen is plagued by subpar acting and a story that defies reason .
arguably akira kurosawa 's masterpiece , the seven samurai is an epic adventure classic with an engrossing story , memorable characters , and stunning action sequences that make it one of the most influential films ever made .
anchored by another winning performance from tom hanks , steven spielberg 's unflinchingly realistic war film virtually redefines the genre .
atonement features strong performances , brilliant cinematography , and a unique score . featuring deft performances from james macavoy and keira knightley , it 's a successful adaptation of ian mcewan 's novel .
some filmgoers may be surprised by the farrellys ' defense of traditional domestic values in hall pass -- unfortunately , they 'll probably also be dismayed by the absence of laughs .
hustle & flow is gritty and redemptive , with a profound sense of place and exciting music .
with its epic story and breathtaking visuals , princess mononoke is a landmark in the world of animation .
a frantic and occasional funny adaptation of douglas adams ' novel . however , it may have those unfamiliar with the source material scratching their heads .
with its impeccably slow-building story and a cast for the ages , the great escape is an all-time action classic .
orlando ca n't match its visual delights with equally hefty narrative -- but it 's so much fun to watch that it does n't need to .
it might be hard for most viewers to identify with the company men 's well-heeled protagonists , but writer/director john wells uses their plight to make universally resonant points -- and gets the most out of his excellent cast .
featuring outstanding work from an excellent cast that includes jack nicholson , leonardo dicaprio , and matt damon , the departed is a thoroughly engrossing gangster drama with the gritty authenticity and soupy morality that has infused director martin scorsese 's past triumphs .
yogi bear 's 3d effects and all-star voice cast are cold comfort for its aggressively mediocre screenplay .
featuring some of the best french actresses working today , 8 women is frothy , delirious , over-the-top fun .
it 's pure formula , but thanks to its breezy pace and a pair of charming performances from tom cruise and cameron diaz , knight and day offers some agreeably middle-of-the-road summer action .
managing to be both satirical and warm-hearted in its look at the inhabitants of a commune , together successfully captures the spirit of a time .
a notorious stinker , from justin to kelly features banal songs , a witless plot , and non-existent chemistry between its american idol-sanctioned leads .
despite being somewhat more exciting than the previous film , this kiddy flick still lacks any real adventure or excitement . what is does contain is choppy animation and poor voice acting . does n't match up to virtually anything out there .
poignant documentary that 's hard to forget .
a clever parody of cop-buddy action-comedies , the other guys delivers several impressive action set pieces and lots of big laughs , thanks to the assured comic chemistry between will ferrell and mark wahlberg .
it may prove frustratingly slow for some viewers , but more contemplative filmgoers will find themselves rewarded by the patience stone 's quietly fierce storytelling , as well as a searing starring turn from golshifteh farahani .
a powerfully visceral docu-drama highlighting the evils of censorship and the essential need for freedom of speech .
atmospheric , great sets and costumes , but thin plot .
it has perhaps aged poorly , but this languidly paced wwii romance remains an iconic , well-acted film , featuring particularly strong performances from burt lancaster and montgomery clift .
lovely to look at but about as intelligent as the asteroid that serves as the movie 's antagonist , armageddon slickly sums up the cinematic legacies of producer jerry bruckheimer and director michael bay .
empathetically written , splendidly acted , and beautifully photographed , ida finds director pawel pawlikowski revisiting his roots to powerful effect .
aside from its clichéd resolution , disturbia is a tense , subtle thriller with a noteworthy performance from shia labeouf .
dynamic , tightly arranged , and deliberately provocative , joe berlinger 's crude is a sobering , enraging wake-up call .
jonah teaches wholesome messages to children in a funny , bouncy package .
a well-constructed b-movie thriller , joy ride keeps up the necessary level of tension and chills . critics also liked zahn 's performance as the goofball older brother .
lords of dogtown , while slickly made and edited , lacks the depth and entertaining value of the far superior documentary on the same subject , dogtown and z-boys .
magic mike xxl has enough narrative thrust and beefy charm to deliver another helping of well-oiled entertainment , even if this sequel is n't quite as pleasurable as its predecessor .
though steven soderbergh succeeds in emulating the glossy look of 1940s noirs , the good german ultimately ends up as a self-conscious exercise in style that forgets to develop compelling characters .
the animation is lovely , but the plot is complex to the point of inscrutability , leaving ghost in the shell 2 : innocence both original and numbing .
a bronx tale sets itself apart from other coming-of-age dramas thanks to a solid script , a terrific cast , and director robert de niro 's sensitive work behind the camera .
a beguiling tragicomedy , vicky cristina barcelona charms with beautiful views of the spanish city and a marvelously well-matched cast .
even with the force of a `` classic '' behind it , remake fever ca n't hold up the hollowness of this style-drenched omen .
a meandering , mindless family movie that frequently resorts to special effects and transparent sappiness .
with a charismatic lead , this new shaft knows how to push the right buttons .
the magic is gone , leaving a dreary , generic action movie .
smartly filmed , tightly scripted , and -- most importantly -- consistently frightening , poltergeist is a modern horror classic .
violent images and blunt audience provocation make up this nihilistic experiment from one of cinema 's more difficult filmmakers .
a straightforward , entertaining thriller with a crackerjack performance by edward norton .
light and charming , serendipity could benefit from less contrivances .
grease 2 is undeniably stocked with solid songs and well-choreographed dance sequences , but there 's no getting around the fact that it 's a blatant retread of its far more entertaining predecessor .
despite its familiar themes , the way way back makes use of its talented cast , finely tuned script , and an abundance of charm to deliver a funny and satisfying coming-of-age story .
compelling , well-crafted storytelling and a judicious sense of terror ensure steven spielberg 's jaws has remained a benchmark in the art of delivering modern blockbuster thrills .
the good cast and rollicking soundtrack eventually drown when this comic homage to pirate radio loses its quippy steam .
dmx 's menacing charisma is put to good use in this stylish but hackneyed modern-day noir .
this road-trip movie about an autistic savant and his callow brother is far from seamless , but barry levinson 's direction is impressive , and strong performances from tom cruise and dustin hoffman add to its appeal .
unevenly paced and thoroughly cheesy , barbarella is nonetheless full of humor , entertaining visuals , and jane fonda 's sex appeal .
an involving , if sentimental and predictable family drama elevated by j.k. simmons ' sympathetic lead performance .
kazakh sheep herders get their cinematic due in this lovely , unsentimental debut from director sergei dvortsevoy .
while 30 days of night offers a few thrills , it ultimately succumbs to erratic execution .
brutally honest and utterly compelling , elaine stritch : shoot me offers a riveting , vanity-free portrait of its legendary subject while offering a few essential truths about the human condition .
gleefully nasty and darkly hilarious , cheap thrills lives down to its title in the best possible way .
water lilies is a sharply-observed , provocative coming-of-age story that captures the anxieties of the early teen years .
part real-life thriller , part sobering examination of 21st century civil liberties , citizenfour transcends ideology to offer riveting , must-see cinema .
with exotic locales , impressive special effects , and a worthy central villain , you only live twice overcomes a messy and implausible story to deliver another memorable early bond flick .
a historical account that is equally disturbing and engrossing , with a powerful performance by sylvie testud .
a beautifully-made documentary that explores the challenges and richness of both marriage and art through the lens of a fascinating and complex couple .
a sentimental tale that reveals great emotional truths in american history .
smart , solidly grafted , and thoroughly gripping , barbara offers a deliberately paced , subtly powerful character study .
the powerful singing in amandla makes for an uplifting , compelling documentary .
a cat in paris depicts a stylish , imaginative world with a wonderful soundtrack and hitchcockian overtones .
the first and best pierce brosnan bond film , goldeneye brings the series into a more modern context , and the result is a 007 entry that 's high-tech , action-packed , and urbane .
house of wax is a 3-d horror delight that combines the atmospheric eerieness of the wax museum with the always chilling presence of vincent price .
boosted by sam rockwell 's intense performance , moon is a compelling work of science-fiction , and a promising debut from director duncan jones .
the business of strangers showcases a complex , compelling performance by channing . her interactions and clashes with stiles make for riveting viewing .
based on a powerful true story and led by note-perfect performances from judi dench and steve coogan , philomena offers a profoundly affecting drama for adult filmgoers of all ages .
aardman animations broadens their humor a bit for arthur christmas , a clever and earnest holiday film with surprising emotional strength .
equal parts tough and funny , and led by a perfectly cast burt reynolds , the longest yard has an interesting political subtext and an excellent climax -- even if it takes too long to get there .
a wrenching , quietly violent psychodrama , our children has the courage to ask difficult questions , and the strength to leave the answers to the viewer .
a charming and delightful walk through the hundred acres woods for young viewers .
saint ralph is an amiable tear-jerker that walks a fine line between being inspirational and being hokum .
a landmark sergio leone spaghetti western masterpiece featuring a classic morricone score .
serving up a fresh round of over-the-top thrills while adding unexpected dramatic heft , furious 7 keeps the franchise moving in more ways than one .
overcomes its formulaic storyline thanks to anthony hopkins ' warm and endearing portrayal of an age-defying thrill seeker .
taking place in a hotel room , tape has the feel of a play , but its engrossing psychodrama allows its stars to shine .
while ang lee 's ambitious film earns marks for style and an attempt at dramatic depth , there 's ultimately too much talking and not enough smashing .
shakespeare gets the deluxe space treatment in forbidden planet , an adaptation of the tempest with impressive sets and seamless special effects .
a charming tale of a love affair that overcomes cultural taboos .
tries to be high-minded , but in the end , it 's just a stylish action movie .
critics praise woody allen 's sweet and lowdown for its charming , light-hearted comedy and quality acting .
by turns touching and funny , this norwegian import offers quietly absorbing commentary on modern life and friendship .
